<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,870,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
[TL: Southern 
<collectingCountry box="[810,1029,870,897]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
] is considered by the authors to be a lightly marked but brightly coloured variety 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[658,777,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[658,777,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with reduced black markings on both wing surfaces. This nomenclatural association agrees with those of 
<bibRefCitation author="Higgins, L. G." box="[683,903,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins (1941: 331</bibRefCitation>
, plate 14, fig. 9), 
<bibRefCitation author="Tshikolovets, V. V." box="[1101,1384,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" refId="ref11624" refString="Tshikolovets, V. V. (2011) Butterflies of Europe &amp; the Mediterranean area. Tshikolovets Publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 544 pp." type="book" year="2011">Tshikolovets (2011: 497)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." pageId="1" pageNumber="26" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 60)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[553,877,979,1005]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 43</bibRefCitation>
, note 9), with which the present authors agree.
</paragraph>
